[2026-04-03 session] The purpose is to maintain a schedule of assignments of restaurant workers to restaurant stations at particular timeslots. I need to be able to enter all the necessary data via an admin interface and save it to a database. I need to be able to create an initial assignment (more on that later). I need to be able to incrementally update the schedule in response to various events (more on that later). All assignments are subject to business rules such as staying within the allowed number of works hours per week of the worker, or not scheduling a worker for consecutive slots that are too close together in time. Workers have particular skills. Stations require particular skills. Workers have employment status (full-time, part-time, on-call) with a limit to hours they can work per week, but sometimes with the option of working overtime. The slots represent the hours the restaurant is open. An assignment is a (worker, station, slot) triple. Workers have preferences such as whether they are open to working overtime, or which stations they prefer. Workers can be out for various reasons such as injury/illness, rehabilition, vacation, off-site training. Some of these activities must be requested in advance. The schedule is prepared a month at a time a few weeks before the start of a month, and must take into account upcoming absences as well as all of the other constraints. I would like initially to interact via a web browser, but eventually also by mobile phone or tablet. I want the backend to be layered for ease of constructing tests. Specifically, the data layer should support a full-featured database for production, but also sqlite for testing. The web interface should be as straightforward as possible initially, but should allow developing more sophisticated views and styles if desired. The backend should be in Haskell. I am particularly interesting in modeling the domain in terms of a formal algebra of terminal units, operations that can be performed on them, and algebraic laws that the operations follow.
